<h2 style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; font-family: 'Open Sans'; font-size: 22px; line-height: 28.8px; margin: 0.67em 0px;">
Some factors to keep in mind for JEE exams</h2>
<div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: 'open sans'; font-size: 16px; line-height: 32px; margin-bottom: 5px;">
</div>
<div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: 'open sans'; font-size: 16px; line-height: 32px; margin-bottom: 5px;">
<span style="box-sizing: border-box;"><b>Proper Planning</b></span><span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 600;">:&nbsp;</span>Usually, students study for about 1 or 2 years to prepare for IIT-JEE. So, planning plays an important role. A good planning strategy will keep you focused and result in better gains. Make a to-do list, set your goals, work out how much time is needed to achieve them, and allocate a realistic time frame. See if you are able to achieve them, if yes, set more ambitious goals next time, if not, analyse what went wrong and how you can improve. I am sure you would be able to crack the JEE&nbsp;in the coming years.<br />
<br /></div>
